<br>
Find more maps at the Online Version of the <a
 href="http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/cuba.html">
Perry-Casta&ntilde;eda Library Map Collection</a> at the University of
Texas. Find more detailed maps at <a href="http://www.cubamapa.com/">
Cuba Mapa.Com</a> . The flag of Cuba (top of page) was officially
adopted on May 20, 1902.
The overall design is modeled after the U.S. and Texas flags. The red
triangle
is from the Masonic symbol for equality. La Estrella Solitaria, or the
white
Lone Star, is placed on the triangle.<br>
